        },
        {
          id: "0300000001700002",
          type: "item",
          item: "tconstruct:tool_handle_cast"
        }
      ],
      description: ["Now that we have our basic smeltery up and running, the first thing we'll need to make is casts for the tool parts we're going to be making.", "", "Now you can make the casts out of clay if you wish, but they only last for one use.", "", "We are, however, going to make the sturdier ones made out of &lAluminum Brass &rwhich will be reusable.", "", "We'll need 1 &lCopper&r to 3 &lAluminum&r in the smeltery. That will make 4 ingots. To make our casts now that we have &lAluminum Brass&r, we need a few tool parts made from the parts table. Right click it into the &l'Casting Table'&r and then right click on the faucet. It will start pouring the cast over the tool part (It &lWILL&r consume the tool part so make sure it's not made of something valuable). It will only use one ingot, so you will have 3 more casts worth of &lAluminum Brass&r. Let's make those and we can move on to the next quest."],
      icon: "tconstruct:pick_head_cast",
      dependencies: ["02000000016E0000"],
      rewards: [
